---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Westside: The 500 Cr Scale | Yatish Shirsath">
  
  <div class="fixed top-0 left-0 h-1 bg-black z-50 w-full scale-x-0 animate-[progress_1s_ease-out_forwards] origin-left"></div>

  <header class="relative min-h-[90vh] flex flex-col justify-end p-6 md:p-12 overflow-hidden bg-[#F5F5F3]">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0 opacity-10 grayscale" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1483985988355-763728e1935b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto w-full">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end justify-between gap-8 border-b border-black pb-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4 block text-gray-500">Case Study 01 • TATA Enterprise</span>
          <h1 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-5xl md:text-8xl leading-[0.9] text-black italic">
            Fashioning<br/> <span class="not-italic font-bold">Scale.</span>
          </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-md">
          <p class="text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed font-medium text-gray-800">
            Orchestrating the UX strategy—from <span class="border-b border-black">gamified carts</span> to <span class="border-b border-black">luxury microsites</span>—to fuel Westside's journey toward the <strong>500 Cr Revenue Milestone</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">
        <div>
          <span class="block text-gray-400 mb-1">Role</span>
          <span class="text-black font-bold">Design Manager</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="block text-gray-400 mb-1">Team</span>
          <span class="text-black font-bold">4 Designers</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="block text-gray-400 mb-1">Focus</span>
          <span class="text-black font-bold">Omnichannel Growth</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="block text-gray-400 mb-1">Year</span>
          <span class="text-black font-bold">2024-25</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-16">
        
        <div class="md:col-span-4 md:sticky md:top-32 h-fit">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-red-600 uppercase tracking-widest block mb-4">01 • The Diagnosis</span>
          <h2 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight mb-6">
            Forensic<br/> <span class="italic text-gray-400">Analysis.</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            We didn't guess. We audited. Using <strong>Microsoft Clarity heatmaps</strong>, <strong>Shopify Analytics</strong>, and over 500+ <strong>Play Store reviews</strong>, we identified the specific friction points bleeding revenue.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-gray-600 rounded-full">MS Clarity</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-gray-600 rounded-full">GA4</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-gray-600 rounded-full">Heuristic Eval</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-12">
          
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 border-t border-gray-100 pt-8">
            <div class="w-12 text-2xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic text-red-500">A</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Information Overload & Scroll Fatigue</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
                Heatmaps showed users dropping off after the 3rd horizontal scroll on banner carousels. There was no clear engagement path, just visual noise.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-gray-100 aspect-[2/1] rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-gray-400 text-xs font-mono">
                [Snapshot: Homepage Heatmap showing drop-offs]
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 border-t border-gray-100 pt-8">
            <div class="w-12 text-2xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic text-red-500">B</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The "Guest" Dead-End</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
                Analytics revealed high bounce rates at checkout for guest users. The lack of login incentives was costing us not just sales, but valuable customer data.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 border-t border-gray-100 pt-8">
            <div class="w-12 text-2xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic text-red-500">C</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Search Failure</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                Users searching for "Red Kurta" were getting generic results. The lack of AI-driven context was leading to "0 results" frustration.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#F9F9F9]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16 max-w-2xl">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-widest block mb-4">02 • The Strategy</span>
        <h2 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight mb-6">
          Designing for <span class="italic text-blue-600">Revenue.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">
          We moved beyond "making it pretty" to "making it perform." We implemented specific psychological triggers and functional upgrades to boost Average Order Value (AOV).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        
        <div class="md:row-span-2 bg-white p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-500 group">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-50 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-blue-600 mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-['Playfair_Display'] font-bold mb-4">Gamifying the Cart</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
            To increase AOV, we introduced a progress bar in the cart: <em>"Add ₹900 more for free shipping."</em> This simple gamification nudge significantly lifted basket sizes.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-100 aspect-square rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center text-gray-400 text-xs font-mono">
            [Image: Cart Progress Bar UI]
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-500">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Guest -> Member</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs mb-4">
            Strategically placed login prompts with "Member Price" incentives converted guest users into registered database entries.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-100 h-32 rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center text-gray-400 text-xs font-mono">
            [Image: Login Prompt Modal]
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-500">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">AI-Powered Search</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs mb-4">
            Replaced the legacy search with an AI engine that understands intent (e.g., "Party wear for kids") rather than just keywords.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-2 bg-slate-900 text-white p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center overflow-hidden relative">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-yellow-500 rounded-full blur-[80px] opacity-20"></div>
          <div class="flex-1 relative z-10">
            <span class="text-yellow-400 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-2 block">Loyalty Revamp</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic mb-4">WestStyle Club</h3>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
              We redesigned the coupon experience. Instead of hiding codes, we made them "Opt-in" with one tap. This transparency built trust and increased redemption rates.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 aspect-video bg-white/10 rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center text-white/30 text-xs font-mono">
            [Image: WSC Dashboard]
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-32 bg-[#0F0F0F] text-[#F5F5F3] relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-purple-900/20 rounded-full blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="text-center mb-20">
        <span class="inline-block border border-white/20 px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-6 text-white/60">Expansion Strategy</span>
        <h2 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-6">The Luxury Pivot.</h2>
        <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-white/60 text-lg font-light leading-relaxed">
          Westside isn't just mass market anymore. We designed distinct, elevated digital identities for three new premium segments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
        
        <div class="group cursor-default">
          <div class="aspect-[4/5] bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-4 mb-6 relative overflow-hidden">
             <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-black/80 opacity-60"></div>
             <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4">
                <p class="text-xs tracking-widest text-white/70 uppercase">Fine Jewellery</p>
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic">Whitedoor</h3>
             </div>
             <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs tracking-widest text-white/20 font-mono">[Image: Whitedoor UI]</div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed border-l border-white/20 pl-4">
            Lab-grown diamonds. The UI focused on "Sparkle" using high-contrast dark modes and macro photography layouts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group cursor-default md:mt-16">
          <div class="aspect-[4/5] bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-4 mb-6 relative overflow-hidden">
             <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-black/80 opacity-60"></div>
             <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4">
                <p class="text-xs tracking-widest text-white/70 uppercase">Luxury Bags</p>
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic">Pome</h3>
             </div>
             <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs tracking-widest text-white/20 font-mono">[Image: Pome UI]</div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed border-l border-white/20 pl-4">
            Positioned as accessible luxury. We utilized video backgrounds and 360-degree product views to mimic the in-store feel.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group cursor-default">
          <div class="aspect-[4/5] bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-4 mb-6 relative overflow-hidden">
             <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-black/80 opacity-60"></div>
             <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4">
                <p class="text-xs tracking-widest text-white/70 uppercase">Premium Apparel (>10k)</p>
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic">Samoh</h3>
             </div>
             <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs tracking-widest text-white/20 font-mono">[Image: Samoh UI]</div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed border-l border-white/20 pl-4">
            A brand for special occasions. The UX prioritized "Look the Look" functionality and rich fabric storytelling.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        
        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-600 uppercase tracking-widest block mb-4">03 • Execution</span>
          <h2 class="font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6 leading-tight">
            Bridging the <br/> Technical Gap.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            The biggest challenge wasn't design; it was execution. The IT team struggled with complex modern layouts. Instead of compromising quality, I stepped into a <strong>Design-Led Engineering</strong> role.
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-8">
            <li class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-gray-100">
              <span class="absolute -left-[9px] top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-indigo-600 rounded-full"></span>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Code as a Deliverable</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">I didn't just send PNGs. I wrote and handed off HTML/CSS snippets for complex interactions, ensuring the live site matched the Figma pixel-perfectly.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-gray-100">
              <span class="absolute -left-[9px] top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-gray-300 rounded-full"></span>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Rigorous QC Rituals</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Instituted a "Design QC" phase before UAT. We logged bugs in trackers and sat with developers weekly to resolve them, prioritizing function over form.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-gray-100">
              <span class="absolute -left-[9px] top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-gray-300 rounded-full"></span>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Westside Wallet</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">To fix post-purchase frustration, we designed the Westside Wallet for instant refunds, turning a pain point into a retention feature.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="relative">
          <div class="bg-[#1e1e1e] p-6 rounded-lg shadow-2xl rotate-2 hover:rotate-0 transition-transform duration-500">
            <div class="flex gap-2 mb-4">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500"></div>
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></div>
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></div>
            </div>
            <code class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-400">
              <span class="text-purple-400">.westside-card</span> &#123;<br/>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;display: <span class="text-yellow-300">grid</span>;<br/>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: <span class="text-blue-300">repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr))</span>;<br/>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;gap: <span class="text-green-300">1.5rem</span>;<br/>
              &#125;<br/>
              <span class="text-gray-500">// I provided code to ensure grid responsiveness worked perfectly.</span>
            </code>
          </div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-10 -right-4 bg-white border border-gray-200 p-4 shadow-lg max-w-[200px]">
            <p class="font-bold text-2xl text-indigo-600">100%</p>
            <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500">Design Consistency Achieved</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#F5F5F3] border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mb-24 text-center md:text-left">
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-black uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">The Goal</span>
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-['Playfair_Display'] font-bold">500 Cr</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Fueling the Revenue Roadmap</p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-black uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">The Team</span>
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-['Playfair_Display'] font-bold">04</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Designers Mentored</p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-black uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">Stakeholders</span>
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-['Playfair_Display'] font-bold">07+</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Teams Aligned (IT, PWC, Mkt)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-black uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">Expansion</span>
          <h3 class="text-4xl font-['Playfair_Display'] font-bold">03</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">New Brands Launched</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 border-t border-gray-300 pt-16">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-['Playfair_Display'] italic mb-6">Reflections &<br/> Leadership.</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Leading design at Westside wasn't just about UI; it was about organizational change management.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Orchestrating the "Village"</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Delivering at this scale required aligning diverse stakeholders—Brand, Marketing, Customer Communication, and our vendor partners at <strong>PWC</strong>. My role shifted from "creator" to "diplomat," ensuring design intent survived the boardrooms and Jira tickets.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Mentorship as a Multiplier</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Managing a team of 4 designers taught me that my output is no longer my pixels, but *their* growth. By setting up design systems and clear BRD processes, I empowered them to own verticals like Whitedoor and Pome independently.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="py-32 bg-black text-white text-center">
    <a href="/work/luca-faloni" class="group inline-block">
      <span class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 block group-hover:text-white transition-colors">Read Next Case Study</span>
      <h2 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-4xl md:text-6xl italic group-hover:underline decoration-1 underline-offset-8">
        Luca Faloni: <br/> The Logistics Logic
      </h2>
    </a>
  </div>

</Layout>